# Zod Form Validation

Use **Zod** for all form validation. Validate on the **server** inside Server Actions — not with ad-hoc checks or client-only validation.

Submission flow is defined in `server-actions.mdc` (do not duplicate). This rule covers schemas and parsing only.

## Schema location

- Shared schemas: `src/lib/schemas/<name>.js`
- Export the schema and inferred shape if needed elsewhere

```js
// src/lib/schemas/user.js
import { z } from "zod";

export const updateUserSchema = z.object({
  userId: z.string().uuid("Invalid user."),
  roleName: z.enum(["default", "admin", "super_admin"], {
    error: "Select a valid role.",
  }),
  enabled: z
    .enum(["true", "false"])
    .transform((value) => value === "true"),
});
```

## Parse FormData in actions

```js
"use server";

import { updateUserSchema } from "@/lib/schemas/user";

export async function updateUser(prevState, formData) {
  const parsed = updateUserSchema.safeParse({
    userId: formData.get("userId"),
    roleName: formData.get("roleName"),
    enabled: formData.get("enabled"),
  });

  if (!parsed.success) {
    return {
      success: false,
      error: parsed.error.flatten().fieldErrors,
      message: null,
    };
  }

  const { userId, roleName, enabled } = parsed.data;
  // persist, revalidatePath, return success state
}
```

## Action return shape

Use a consistent state object for `useActionState`:

```js
{ success: boolean, error: string | Record<string, string[]> | null, message: string | null }
```

- Single global error: `error: "Please fix the highlighted fields."`
- Field errors: `error: { email: ["Enter a valid email address."] }`
- Display errors in the form with `role="alert"` / `aria-invalid`

## Avoid

- Manual regex or `if (!field)` chains when a Zod schema can express the rule
- Client-only validation as the sole gate — always re-validate in the action
- Duplicating the same schema on client and server unless UX needs instant feedback (server schema is source of truth)
